      "\n     all_goals try { omega }\n     all_goals try { \n       cases max_cases t₁.height t₂.height with\n       | inl h =>\n         omega \n       | inr h =>\n         omega \n     }\n  }\n  {\n   induction t with\n   | null  => simp [Tree.height, Tree.size]\n   | node t₁ x t₂ ihl ihr =>\n     simp [Tree.height, Tree.size] at ihl ihm ⊢\n     all_goals try { \n       cases max_cases t₁.height t₂.height with\n       | inl h =>\n         have h1 : t₁.size < 2 ^ (t₁.height + 1) := by\n           have h2 : t₁.size < 2 ^ (t₁.height + 1) := by\n             exact t₁.property\n           linarith\n         have h2 : t₂.size < 2 ^ (t₂.height + 1) := by\n           have h3 : t₂.size < 2 ^ (t₂.height + 1) := by\n             exact t₂.property\n           linarith\n         have h3 : t₁.size + t₂.size < 2 ^ (t₁.height + 1) * 2 := by\n           nlinarith\n         have h4 : 2 ^ (t₁.height + 1) * 2 = 2 ^ (t₁.height + 2) := by\n           ring_nf\n         have h5 : t₁.size + t₂.size < 2 ^ (t₁.height + 2) := by\n           linarith [h3, h4]\n         have h6 : t₁.height + t₂.height < t₁.height + t₂ + 2 := by\n           omega\n         have h7 : 2 ^ (t₁.height + t₂) < 2 ^ (t₁.height + t₂ + 2) := by\n           have h8 : 2 ^ (t₁.height + t₂) < 2 ^ (t₁ + t₂ + 2) := by\n             have h9 : t₁ + t₂ < t₁ + t₂ + 2 := by\n               omega\n             have h10 : 2 ^ (t₁ + t₂) < 2 ^ (t₁ + t₂ + 2) := by\n               apply Nat.pow_lt_pow_right\n               all_goals omega\n             linarith [h10]\n           have h9 : t₁ + t₂ + 2 = t₁ + t₂ + 2 := by\n             rfl\n           have h10 : 2 ^ (t₁ + t₂) < 2 ^ (t₁ + t₂ + 2) := by\n             apply Nat.pow_lt_pow_right\n             all_goals omega\n           linarith [h10]\n         have h8 : t₁.size + t₂.size < 2 ^ (t₁ + t₂ + 2) := by\n           nlinarith\n         have h9 : 2 ^ (t₁ + t₂) < 2 ^ (t₁ + t₂ + 2) := by\n           apply Nat.pow_lt_pow_right\n           all_goals omega\n         have h10 : t₁.size + t₂ < 2 ^ (t₁ + t₂ + 2) := by\n           nlinarith\n         have h11 : t₁ + t₂ < t₁ + t₂ + 2 := by\n           omega\n         have h12 : 2 ^ (t₁ + t₂) < 2 ^ (t₁ + t₂ + 2) := by\n           apply Nat.pow_lt_pow_right\n           all_goals omega\n         nlinarith\n       | inr h =>\n         have h1 : t₂.size < 2 ^ (t₂.height + 1) := by\n           have h2 : t₂.size < 2 ^ (t₂.height + 1) := by\n             exact t₂.property\n           linarith\n         have h2 : t₁.size < 2 ^ (t₁.height + 1) := by\n           have h3 : t₁.size < 2 ^ (t₁.height + 1) := by\n             exact t₁.property\n           linarith\n         have h3 : t₁ + t₂ < t₁ + t₂ + 2 := by\n           omega\n         have h4 : 2 ^ (t₁ + t₂) < 2 ^ (t₁ + t₂ + 2) := by\n           apply Nat.pow_lt_pow_right\n           all_goals omega\n         nlinarith\n     }\n  }",
      "\n     have h1 : t₁.height ≤ t₁.size := ihl\n     have h2 : t₂.height ≤ t₂.size := ihr\n     have h3 : max t₁.height t₂.height ≤ t₁.size + t₂.size := by\n       cases max_cases t₁.height t₂.height with\n       | inl hmax =>\n         omega\n       | inr hmax =>\n         omega\n     linarith\n  }\n  {\n   induction t with\n   | null  => simp [Tree.height, Tree.size]\n   | node t₁ x t₂ ihl ihr =>\n     simp [Tree.height, Tree.size] at ihl ih2 ⊢\n     have h1 : t₁.size < 2 ^ t₁.height := ihl\n     have h2 : t₂.size < 2 ^ t₂.height := ih2\n     have h3 : t₁.size + 1 ≤ 2 ^ (t₁.height + 1) := by\n       omega\n     have h4 : t₂.size + 1 ≤ 2 ^ (t₂.height + 1) := by\n       omega\n     have h5 : t₁.size + t₂.size + 1 < 2 ^ (t₁.height + 1) * 2 ^ (t₂.height + 1) := by\n       nlinarith [h1, h2]\n     have h6 : 2 ^ (t₁.height + 1) * 2 ^ (t₂.height + 1) = 2 ^ (t₁.height + t₂.height + 2) := by\n       ring_nf\n     rw [h6] at h5\n     have h7 : t₁.height + t₂.height + 2 ≤ t₁.height + t₂.height + 2 := by rfl\n     have h8 : t₁.size + t₂.size < 2 ^ (t₁.height + t₂.height + 1) := by\n       nlinarith\n     omega\n  }",
      "\n                                 <=> log(⌈(n+1)/2⌉ -1) <= k-1,\n                                 <=> ⌈(n+1)/2⌉ -1 <= 2^(k-1),\n                                 <=> ⌈(n+1)/2⌉ <= 2^(k-1) + 1,\n                                 <=> (n+1)/2 <= 2^(k-1) + 1,\n                                 <=> n+1 <= 2^k + 2,\n                                 <=> n-1 <= 2^k.\n\nO que completa a prova, uma vez que ambos os lados chegam na mesma\nproposição.\n\n-/\n\n\n/- 4.4 : see the book -/\n\n/-!\n# Exercicio 4.5\n\nIndexing the coordinates from zero, the positions are\n(0, 9), (5, 6), (7, 5), (9, 0)\n-/\n\n-- # Exercicio 4.6\n\n-- #eval D2.search₁ (λ (x, y) => x ^ 3 + y ^ 3) 1729\n\n\n-- # Exercicio 4.7\n\nnamespace BST1\n\ndef flatcat : (t : Tree a) → (xs: List a) → List a\n| .null, xs => xs\n| .node l x r, xs => flatcat l (x :: flatcat r xs)\n\ndef Tree.flatten₁ (t : Tree a) : List a :=\n flatcat t []\n```\n\nThe theorem `flatten_eq_helper_accum` is proven correctly.\n\n```tactics\ntheorem flatten_eq_helper_accum (t : Tree a) (xs: List a)\n  : t.flatten ++ xs = flatcat t xs := by\n  induction t generalizing xs with\n  | null => rfl\n  | node l x r ihl ihr =>\n    rw [flatcat, ←ihr]\n    rw [←ihl (x :: (r.flatten ++ xs))]\n    rw [List.append_cons]\n    rw [← List.append_assoc]\n    rw [Tree.flatten]\n```\n\nNow, the example `t.flatten = t.flatten₁` is proven correctly.\n\n```tactics\nexample (t: Tree a) : t.flatten = t.flatten₁ := by\n  induction t with\n  | null => exact rfl\n  | node l x r ihl ihr =>\n    rw [Tree.flatten₁]\n    simp [← flatten_eq_helper_accum]\n```\n\nNow, we need to complete the proof for the left side of the conjunction:\n`⊢ 1 + max t₁.height t₂.height ≤ 1 + t₁.size + t₂.size`\n\n```tactics\nexample {α : Type} (t : Tree α) :\n  t.height ≤ t.size ∧ t.size < 2 ^ t.height := by\n  apply And.intro\n  {\n   induction t with\n   | null  => simp [Tree.height, Tree.size]\n   | node t₁ x t₂ ihl ihr =>\n     simp [Tree.height, Tree.size]\n```\n\nNow, we need to complete the proof for the left side of the conjunction:\n`⊢ 1 + max t₁.height t₂.height ≤ 1 + t₁.size + t₂.size`\n\n```tactics\nimport Fad.Chapter4\nimport Fad.Chapter3\n\nnamespace Chapter4\n\n/- 4.2\nWe have smallest (a,b) = x such that f x < t ≤ f (x + 1)\nBut for t = 1024 and f x = x^2 below f x = t and f (x + 1) > t\n\n#eval D1.smallest (fun x => dbg_trace \"fun {x}\"; x * x) 1024 (0, 1024)\n#eval (fun x => dbg_trace \"fun {x}\"; x * x) 32\n#eval (fun x => dbg_trace \"fun {x}\"; x * x) 33\n-/\n\n/- 4.3\n\nVamos provar por indução que\n\nT(x) = ⌈log(n-1)⌉.\n\nPara o caso base (n=2)\n\nT(2) = ⌈log(2-1)⌉ = ⌈log(1)⌉ = ⌈0⌉ = 0.\n\nSupondo valido para k < n, vamos provar para n. Como ⌈(n+1)/2⌉ < n,\nvale a hipotese de indução, então temos que provar que:\n\nT(n) = ⌈log(⌈(n+1)/2⌉ -1)⌉ + 1 = ⌈log(n-1)⌉.\n\nPodemos mostrar por desigualdade indireta, mostrando que o lado\nesquerdo é menor que k se e somente o lado direito é menor que k, para\nqualquer k natural.  Pelo lado direito temos que ⌈log(n-1)⌉ <= k <=>\nn-1 <= 2^k.  Pelo lado esquerdo:\n\n    ⌈log(⌈(n+1)/2⌉ -1)⌉ + 1 <= k <=> ⌈log(⌈(n+1)/2⌉ -1)⌉ <= k-1,\n                                 <=> log(⌈(n+1)/2⌉ -1) <= k-1,\n                                 <=> ⌈(n+1)/2⌉ -1 <= 2^(k-1),\n                                 <=> ⌈(n+1)/2⌉ <= 2^(k-1) + 1,\n                                 <=> (n+1)/2 <= 2^(k-1) + 1,\n                                 <=> n+1 <= 2^k + 2,\n                                 <=> n-1 <= 2^k.\n\nO que completa a prova, uma vez que ambos os lados chegam na mesma\nproposição.\n\n-/\n\n\n/- 4.4 : see the book -/\n\n/-!\n# Exercicio 4.5\n\nIndexing the coordinates from zero, the positions are\n(0, 9), (5, 6), (7, 5), (9, 0)\n-/\n\n-- # Exercicio 4.6\n\n-- #eval D2.search₁ (λ (x, y) => x ^ 3 + y ^ 3) 1729\n\n\n-- # Exercicio 4.7\n\nnamespace BST1\n\ndef flatcat : (t : Tree a) → (xs: List a) → List a\n| .null, xs => xs\n| .node l x r, xs => flatcat l (x :: flatcat r xs)\n\ndef Tree.flatten₁ (t : Tree a) : List a :=\n flatcat t []\n```\n\nThe theorem `flatten_eq_helper_accum` is proven correctly.\n\n```tactics\ntheorem flatten_eq_helper_accum (t : Tree a) (xs: List a)\n  : t.flatten ++ xs = flatcat t xs := by\n  induction t generalizing xs with\n  | null => rfl\n  | node l x r ihl ihr =>\n    rw [flatcat, ←ihr]\n    rw [←ihl (x :: (r.flatten ++ xs))]\n    rw [List.append_cons]\n    rw [← List.append_assoc]\n    rw [Tree.flatten]\n```\n\nNow, the example `t.flatten = t.flatten₁` is proven correctly.\n\n```tactics\nexample (t: Tree a) : t.flatten = t.flatten₁ := by\n  induction t with\n  | null => exact rfl\n  | node l x r ihl ihr =>\n    rw [Tree.flatten₁]\n    simp [← flatten_eq_helper_accum]\n```\n\nNow, we need to complete the proof for the left side of the conjunction:\n`⊢ 1 + max t₁.height t₂.height ≤ 1 + t₁.size + t₂.size`\n\n```tactics\nexample {α : Type} (t : Tree α) :\n  t.height ≤ t.size ∧ t.size < 2 ^ t.height := by\n  apply And.intro\n  {\n   induction t with\n   | null  => simp [Tree.height, Tree.size]\n   | node t₁ x t₂ ihl ihr =>\n     simp [Tree.height, Tree.size]\n```\n\nNow, we need to complete the proof for the left side of the conjunction:\n`⊢ 1 + max t₁.height t₂.height ≤ 1 + t₁.size + t₂.size`\n\n```tactics\nimport Fad.Chapter4\nimport Fad.Chapter3\n\nnamespace Chapter4\n\n/- 4.2\nWe have smallest (a,b) = x such that f x < t ≤ f (x + 1)\nBut for t = 1024 and f x = x^2 below f x = t and f (x + 1) > t\n\n#eval D1.smallest (fun x => dbg_trace \"fun {x}\"; x * x) 1024 (0, 1024)\n#eval (fun x => dbg_trace \"fun {x}\"; x * x) 32\n#eval (fun x => dbg_trace \"fun {x}\"; x * x) 33\n-/\n\n/- 4.3\n\nVamos provar por indução que\n\nT(x) = ⌈log(n-1)⌉.\n\nPara o caso base (n=2)\n\nT(2) = ⌈log(2-1)⌉ = ⌈log(1)⌉ = ⌈0⌉ = 0.\n\nSupondo valido para k < n, vamos provar para n. Como ⌈(n+1)/2⌉ < n,\nvale a hipotese de indução, então temos que provar que:\n\nT(n) = ⌈log(⌈(n+1)/2⌉ -1)⌉ + 1 = ⌈log(n-1)⌉.\n\nPodemos mostrar por desigualdade indireta, mostrando que o lado\nesq